<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7626323>
    dc:description "FIGURE 52. A–F, Percnon gibbesi (H. Milne Edwards, 1853). A, B, Male, cl 16.4 mm, cw 14.8 mm (MZUSP 40168). C, D, Juvenile female, cl 11.9 mm, cw 10.5 mm (MZUSP 40166). E, Ovigerous female, cl 16.1 mm, cw 14.5 mm (MZUSP 33824). Habitus, dorsal (A, C, E) and ventral (B, D) aspects. F, Percnon gibbesi (arrow) in the borehole of the urchin Diadema ascensionis Mortensen. Trindade Island, June 2012. Photographs: (A–E) by A. Pol, (F) by J.B. Mendonça." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7626323/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

